  <title class="- topic/title ">Prepare to Add Segment Filters</title>
  <shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc ">There are several ways to prepare to
	 add segment filters. 
  </shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <othermeta name="solution" content="Target" />
      <othermeta name="topic" content="Advanced" />
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody ">
    <steps id="steps_0BF2D8633CB84B0EB9FA31B9E8D0A941" class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
      <step id="step_9FC830226BF84905B29BFBD04990A988" class="- topic/li task/step ">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Brainstorm on which visitor segments
			 you want to know about. For each segment, choose the right parameter type. 
		  </cmd>
      </step>
      <step id="step_8C66719974724FA4B404335D7E7B345C" class="- topic/li task/step ">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Associate the parameter with the
			 mboxes. 
		  </cmd>
      </step>
      <step id="step_93F26B54222A4C69BFBEE0303E9C609A" class="- topic/li task/step ">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Based on the parameter you will use,
			 decide which action will include a visitor in a segment during the campaign. 
		  </cmd>
        <stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">
          <p class="- topic/p ">Either: 
			 </p>
          <p class="- topic/p ">
            <ul id="ul_2485112A02784CCB99356EC699834520" class="- topic/ul ">
              <li id="li_8854B490468943F6BE4468DF8D8D4679" class="- topic/li "> A
				  visit to an mbox on the entry page of the campaign (a likely choice for
				  segmenting on source) 
				</li>
              <li id="li_D337AF2BD1E94F6FA972BA500CA563A6" class="- topic/li ">
				  Only visitors who reach a certain success metric 
				</li>
              <li id="li_595F2DD952714A658C256116E022F32E" class="- topic/li ">
				  Only visitors who reach conversion 
				</li>
            </ul>
          </p>
        </stepresult>
      </step>
    </steps>
  </taskbody>
